  "text": "• Formal semantics. The composition language should be declarative, implementation independent, and based on a solid formal framework. The need of an underlying formal framework is widely recognized and in particular it is important to i) ensure non-ambiguous behavior, and ii) reason about and prove specifications properties and correctness [CITATION_1] . In our framework this is particular important in the presence of incomplete specifications.",
